body:
I believe rand real is not yet supported. Please consider adding an error. Testcase and log below.

Thanks


```verilog
class my_c;
  rand bit b1;
  rand real r1;
endclass : my_c

module test;
  initial begin
    // Create an instance of the my_c class
    /* verilator lint_off IMPLICITSTATIC */
    my_c my_c_o = new();

    // Attempt to randomize and verify the constraints
    /* verilator lint_off WIDTHTRUNC */
    assert (my_c_o.randomize())
    else $error("Randomization failed!");
  end
endmodule
```
It throws error as below:
```log

Vaf_sv_vlt_rand_real___024unit__03a__03amy_c__Vclpkg__0.cpp:30:23: error: ‘VL_RANDOM_RNG_D’ was not declared in this scope; did you mean ‘VL_RANDOM_RNG_W’?
   30 |     this->__PVT__r1 = VL_RANDOM_RNG_D(__Vm_rng);
      |                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                       VL_RANDOM_RNG_W
```

